------STEP 1: Add Font Awesome (Eye Icon Library)

Open your login.blade.php and register.blade.php
Add this inside <head> section:

<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.0/css/all.min.css">
 STEP 2: Login Page ‚Äì Eye Icon Inside Password Input

Update your password field in
resources/views/login.blade.php

<style>
.password-box {
    position: relative;
    width: 300px;
}

.password-box input {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 10px;
    padding-right: 40px;
}

.password-box i {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    right: 10px;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    cursor: pointer;
    color: gray;
}
</style>

<label>Password:</label><br>
<div class="password-box">
    <input type="password" id="loginPassword" name="password" required>
    <i class="fa-solid fa-eye" onclick="toggleLoginPassword()"></i>
</div>
<br><br>

Add this script before </body>:

<script>
function toggleLoginPassword() {
    var pass = document.getElementById("loginPassword");
    var icon = event.target;

    if (pass.type === "password") {
        pass.type = "text";
        icon.classList.remove("fa-eye");
        icon.classList.add("fa-eye-slash");
    } else {
        pass.type = "password";
        icon.classList.remove("fa-eye-slash");
        icon.classList.add("fa-eye");
    }
}
</script>
 STEP 3: Register Page ‚Äì Eye Icon for Both Password Fields

Open:
resources/views/register.blade.php

Replace password section:

<style>
